At 04:59 PM 10/25/2004, Richard Atwell wrote:

 

>The 72 bus that just seized has an a/c compressor installed. The weird 

>thing is that the pulley is on the oil cooler side. The belt isn't 

>hooked up and I can't figure out in my head how it would have been 

>driven by the main pulley. Was it installed backwards?

 

Richard,

         The setup is correct.  The belt goes in FRONT of the fan housing
(between the housing and the engine) and connects to a pulley behind the fan
hub.  It would be a decent system if it used a standard sized belt.

 

>This is an a/c setup I've never seen before. The evaporator is under 

>the jump seat behind the driver and there is a huge condenser under the 

>body with two electric fans. There are VPC logos on the evaporator.

 

I have heard of that type before, but never laid eyes on one.

 

-David
